  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\nMax fee to send 10 ETH is shown as \"0.0008232\" and later is shown as \"0.0008232392\" if edit the sum. If re-open screen Send transaction then again \"0.0008232\" is shown as max fee. It happens for non-default fee (e.g. max of min values). I would expect same fee with same precision shown for the same sum.\r\n\r\n![changed fee to max](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/28471498-96ab801c-6e3d-11e7-80d3-0cd8a2fc2f99.png)\r\n\r\n![changed sum back](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/28471630-118850ee-6e3e-11e7-9601-e704c9ad3d97.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n same fee with same precision shown for the same sum.\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nMax fee to send 10 ETH is shown as \"0.0008232\" and later is shown as \"0.0008232392\" if edit the sum. \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nvideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=0Bz3t9zSg1wb7ZkIwSmVpMkVXRVU\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open 1-1 chat\r\n- send to a contact 10 Ether to get Send transaction screen with Fee\r\n- move fee to be of a max or min value. In my case, I moved to to the most right position (Faster)\r\n- remember the Fee value shown\r\n- edit sum to be sent: make it \"1\". As a result, fee value is changed\r\n- edit sum again and put it back to initial \"10\". Check the value for fee\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: develop 0.9.8-89-g20550b42+\r\n* Operating System: \r\nReal device Samsung Galaxy S6, Android 6.0.1\r\nReal device iPhone 6s, iOS 10.2.1",
